    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-01-19T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-01-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="430"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d430">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">868.51 War Credits/650</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Atherton</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 444</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-01-19">January 19,
                            1934</date>.<lb/>[Received January 26.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to the Embassy’s despatch No. 391 of
                    December 19<note n="2" xml:id="d430fn2">Not printed.</note> with respect to the
                    agreement announced on November 17, 1933, concerning the external indebtedness
                    of Greece, between representatives of the Greek Government, the League Loans
                    Committee (London) and the Council of Foreign Bondholders, I understand that no
                    actual payment has yet been made to the bondholders of the Greek Government 6%
                    stabilization and refugee loan of 1928. At the Embassy’s request, however,
                    Hambros Bank Limited, 41 Bishopsgate, London, E. C. 2, has agreed to forward it
                    a copy of any notice relative to the partial payment of the coupons of this
                    loan, whenever it is in a position to do so.</p>
                <p>As of interest in this connection there is enclosed a copy of an article from the
                        <hi rend="italic">Times</hi> of January 19<note n="3" xml:id="d430fn3">Not
                        reprinted.</note> on the subject of the League loans, written by Sir Austen
                    Chamberlain, Chairman of the League Loans Committee (London).</p>
                <p>Respectfully yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Ray Atherton</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
